---
description: "FastAPI backend conventions"
globs: ["app/**/*.py"]
alwaysApply: false
---
All chat endpoints stream via SSE. ChatOrchestrator.handle_message() returns AsyncIterator[str].

FastAPI dependencies use Depends() for injection. ModelScheduler, Settings, and service instances are singletons created in lifespan.

Use httpx.AsyncClient for all HTTP calls. Close clients in lifespan shutdown.

Logging uses named loggers: prompter.router, prompter.rag, prompter.llm, prompter.search, prompter.embedding, prompter.mcp, prompter.scheduler.

Error responses use standard FastAPI HTTPException with appropriate status codes.

Test files live in tests/ and use pytest + pytest-asyncio. Every new module gets a corresponding test file.